BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:2kTLCCSDC1Gg4hFDe7GTU
SUMMARY:Anila Quayyum Agha: Geometry of Light
DTSTAMP:20260327T033913Z
DTSTART:20260404T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Anila Quayyum Agha: Geometry of Light invites you to become par
	t of the art. Agha\, a Pakistani American artist\, animates spaces with he
	r large-scale sculptural installations. Suspended from the ceiling\, Agha’
	s steel cubes are laser-cut with intricate designs that project geometric 
	shadows onto the visitor. She draws on both the light and dark of her own 
	life\, using South Asian art practices to convey the gender discrimination
	 she faced growing up as a young girl in Pakistan. An in-depth exploration
	 of Islamic architecture\, art\, and identity\, this is the first solo exh
	ibition of a Pakistani American artist in SAM’s 90-year history. Agha is c
	arving a name out for herself in the art world—visit the Seattle Asian Art
	 Museum for an immersive and illuminating experience.\n\nhttps://seatoday.
	6amcity.com/events/#/details/anila-quayyum-agha-geometry-of-light/16795597
	/2026-04-04T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/anila-quayyum-agha-geomet
	ry-of-light/16795597/2026-04-04T00
LOCATION:Seattle Art Museum\, 1300 First Avenue\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:0Zig_kDnSagxZIcjaK3ti
SUMMARY:CL 101: Intro to Concert Lighting
DTSTAMP:20260327T033913Z
DTSTART:20260404T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:In this 2-hour workshop\, students will have a practical grasp 
	on lighting concepts and console operation\, learn about different lightin
	g instruments\, and gain hands-on experience programming lights for Vera’s
	 mainstage. Participants of the class will also gain basic fundamental kno
	wledge of working with artists and production staff to elevate the concert
	 experience as a lighting engineer.\n\nComplete this class to be eligible 
	for Lighting Engineer volunteer shifts at Vera shows. Become a volunteer a
	t Vera to access other production-related opportunities!\n\nhttps://link.d
	ice.fm/l92cff65454f\n\nFrom The Vera Project
URL:https://link.dice.fm/l92cff65454f
LOCATION:305 Harrison Street\, Seattle\, Washington 98109\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:vera-project
CATEGORIES:The Vera Project
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:69ZrkMhfRC7umUVVQBeUb
SUMMARY:Spring Educator Workshop: Seeing Self and Place in the Modern North
	west
DTSTAMP:20260327T033913Z
DTSTART:20260404T173000Z
DESCRIPTION:Explore the symbolic and deeply personal visions of artists who
	 helped define a unique modernist movement in the Pacific Northwest. Cente
	ring Beyond Mysticism: The Modern Northwest\, educators will gain insight 
	on how artists blended abstraction and nature to express complex ideas abo
	ut identity\, place\, and purpose. Participants will engage in a studio ar
	t activity inspired by the exhibition\, explore student-led inquiry models
	\, and reflect and connect with fellow educators. Tickets This workshop is
	 free to attend\, but reservations are required. This workshop includes re
	sources and Washington State Clock Hours. K-12 educators\, paraeducators\,
	 subject area coaches\, and administrators are welcome to attend. Support 
	for K-12 programs during the 2025-2026 school year is provided by the Fost
	er Foundation. Partial\, sustained support for SAM's K-12 programs is prov
	ided by an endowment established in 1999 by a National Endowment for the H
	umanities challenge grant and the generous contributions of matching donor
